
[1]carrion

   CARRION, n.

   1. The dead and putrefying body or flesh of animals; flesh so corrupted
   as to be unfit for food.

   2. A worthless woman; a term of reproach.

      CARRION, a. Relating to dead and putrefying carcasses; feeding on
                         carrion, as a carrion-crow.
